          {
            "commit": "d53b6a243ecee5ef05510b914a19c28f17b1d320",
            "subject": "LU-18456 tcu: update LinkEA when move file into Trash Can"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Qian Yingjin",
          "email": "qian@ddn.com",
          "date": "2025-05-02 01:45:49.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Qian Yingjin",
          "email": "qian@ddn.com",
          "date": "2025-10-23 08:19:31.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-18958 tcu: add NOTRASH flag for files and directories",
        "message": "LU-18958 tcu: add NOTRASH flag for files and directories\n\nAdd a NOTRASH attribute to a file or directory, so that when it is\ndeleted the MDS will bypass the Trash Can completely and delete\nthe file immediately (as it was without the Trash Can feature).\n\nIf the NOTRASH attribute is set on a directory, then new files in\nthat directory will inherit the NOTRASH attribute.\n\nThis is intended to mark directories that contain very temporary\nfiles that should not consume space in the Trash Can.\n\nAdd the command to set/clear trash flags (i.e. NOTRASH) on given\nfiles or directories:\nlfs chattr [-RVH] [+notrash|+n] [-notrash|-n] FILE [...]\nor\nchattr [-RV] [+d] [-d] FILE [...]\nAdd the command to display the trash state and information for\ngiven files or directories:\nlfs trash state FILE [...]\nlsattr FILE\n\nAdd sanityn/test_117o to verify it works as expected.\n\nSigned-off-by: Yingjin Qian <qian@ddn.com>\nSigned-off-by: Artem Blagodarenko <ablagodarenko@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I4e232c4aead9a1bffe7f061dba574497cf719ec6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
